ot its name from Latin <i>laurus</i> ‘laurel’, although it is more probably of pre-Roman origin. The given name was moderately popular in the Middle Ages (when it was used for girls as well as boys), under the influence of a 3rd-century saint who was one of the seven deacons of Rome. He was martyred in  258 . The legend is that, having been required to hand over the Church's treasures to the civil authorities, he assembled the poor and sick and presented them. For this act of Christian defiance, he was roasted to death on a gridiron. In England the name is also associated with  St Laurence of Canterbury  (  d. 619 ). A more recent influence has been the actor  Sir Laurence Olivier  (  1907–89 ).  See also  Lawrence ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Lars Birgersson Lilja was born about 1360, in Sweden, his father, Birger Johnsson Lilja, was 32 and his mother, Ramborg Karlsdotter, was 36. He had at least 1 son with Ramborg Germundsdotter. He died on 3 February 1404, at the age of 45."},"et":{"about 1360–3 Feb 1404":"umbes 1360–3. veebruar 1404","1360–1404":"1360–1404","1375–1423":"1375–1423","1400–1459":"1400–1459","1330–Male":"1330–Surnud","1325–1374":"1325–1374","1459":"1459","1404":"1404","about 1360":"umbes 1360","1325":"1325","1423":"1423","1400":"1400","1375":"1375","1374":"1374","1330":"1330","3 Feb 1404":"3. veebruar 1404","1360":"1360","Linköping, Östergötland, Sweden":"Linköping, Östergötland, Rootsi","Sweden":"Rootsi","Floda, Södermanland, Sweden":"Floda, Södermanland, Rootsi"},"fi":{"about 1360–3 Feb 1404":"noin 1360–3. helmikuuta 1404","1360–1404":"1360–1404","1375–1423":"1375–1423","1400–1459":"1400–1459","1330–Male":"1330–Kuollut","1325–1374":"1325–1374","1459":"1459","1404":"1404","about 1360":"noin 1360","1325":"1325","1423":"1423","1400":"1400","1375":"1375","1374":"1374","1330":"1330","3 Feb 1404":"3. helmikuuta 1404","1360":"1360","Linköping, Östergötland, Sweden":"Linköping, Östergötland, Ruotsi","Sweden":"Ruotsi","Floda, Södermanland, Sweden":"Floda, S